<h2>Instruction summary<br /></h2>
<p>Your research data will be stored in a permanent and sustainable manner, according to the guidelines of the international <a class="external" href="http://www.datasealofapproval.org/" target="_blank">Data Seal of Approval</a>. Please note the <a class="external" href="http://www.dans.knaw.nl/sites/default/files/file/archief/Preferred_formats.pdf" target="_blank">Preferred formats</a> (pdf). When you are depositing data, you can determine to what extent the data will be accessible. If you opt for Open access, it means that your data are accessible to registered users of EASY. You can also opt for Restricted access, which means that permission is required before the data can be used.<br />&#160;<br />After depositing the data, you will receive a <a class="external" href="http://www.dans.knaw.nl/en/content/dans-licence-agreement-deposited-data" target="_blank">Licence agreement</a> by E-mail, in which the agreements on access to the data are laid down. You will also receive information about the assignment of a <a class="external" href="http://www.dans.knaw.nl/en/content/persistent-identifier" target="_blank">Persistent Identifier</a> to your dataset. Use of the Persistent Identifier will locate your dataset even after many years, in spite of changes to Internet addresses. <br />After several workdays, your dataset will be published by a DANS staff member. The dataset is then available to other researchers, in accordance with the conditions indicated by you.</p>
